# Claude / Donna runtime
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# Main loop runs Haiku 4.5 by default (cost). Override only to experiment.
DONNA_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
DONNA_REQUEST_TIMEOUT_S=45
DONNA_TRACE_FILE=donna_traces.jsonl
DONNA_SESSION_STORE=.donna_sessions.json
DONNA_USER_ID=local-dev
DONNA_GATE_LOG=donna_gate.jsonl

# LangSmith (optional)
LANGSMITH_TRACING=false
LANGSMITH_API_KEY=lsv2_...
LANGSMITH_PROJECT=donna-dev

# Database. Postgres (docker-compose default) OR SQLite for offline/local dev
# with no Docker — just set: DATABASE_URL=sqlite+aiosqlite:///./donna.db
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://donna:donna@localhost:5432/donna

# Supermemory
SUPERMEMORY_API_KEY=sm_...

# FalkorDB (docker-compose default)
FALKORDB_HOST=localhost
FALKORDB_PORT=6379
FALKORDB_USERNAME=
FALKORDB_PASSWORD=

# OpenAI (Graphiti embedder)
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# WhatsApp Cloud API
WHATSAPP_TOKEN=
WHATSAPP_PHONE_NUMBER_ID=
# No default — must be set, or webhook verification fails closed.
WHATSAPP_VERIFY_TOKEN=
# Meta App Secret. When set, POST /webhook verifies X-Hub-Signature-256.
WHATSAPP_APP_SECRET=

# Webhook routing
# RELAY_URL: when set, the entire webhook is forwarded to this URL and
#   nothing is processed locally. Use for full-mirroring.
# DEV_RELAY_URL + DEV_PHONE_NUMBERS: per-phone re-routing. Set both on the
#   instance that owns the public Meta webhook URL. Webhooks whose `from`
#   matches DEV_PHONE_NUMBERS (comma-separated, no `+`) are peeled off and
#   forwarded to DEV_RELAY_URL/webhook (e.g. ngrok tunnel to localhost),I am unhappy with the current Donna UI.

The implementation is clean, but it feels like a dashboard.

It looks like a well-executed productivity app rather than a category-defining AI companion.

I want a complete visual redesign while preserving the existing functionality.

Do NOT simply restyle the existing cards.

Rethink the information hierarchy from first principles.

---

## CORE PRODUCT TRUTH

Donna is not an assistant.

Donna is not a chatbot.

Donna is not a productivity tracker.

Donna is a thinking partner.

The primary feeling when opening the app should be:

"someone has been paying attention."

Every design decision should reinforce that feeling.

The user should feel understood before they feel organized.

The current design feels operational.

I want it to feel personal.

---

## DESIGN REFERENCES

Reference the emotional quality of:

* Apple Journal
* Arc Browser
* Readwise Reader
* Notion Calendar
* Day One
* Humane interfaces
* High-end editorial magazines

Do NOT reference:

* Linear
* Jira
* Asana
* ClickUp
* Notion dashboards
* CRM software
* Analytics products

The experience should feel editorial rather than software-like.

---

BIGGEST CHANGE:
REMOVE THE CARD STACK MENTALITY
-------------------------------

The current UI is:

Card
Card
Card
Card
Card

This makes the product feel generic.

Reduce card usage by at least 60%.

Many sections should simply live on the page naturally.

Use whitespace and typography for hierarchy.

Not boxes.

Example:

Instead of:

[Open Loops Card]

Show:

OPEN LOOPS

reply to luca

antler intro form

call mom

with generous spacing and subtle dividers.

Think newspaper.
Think journal.
Think editorial layout.

---

## THESIS-FIRST DESIGN

The daily thesis should become the hero of the application.

Current:

today is about the antler deck.
everything else can wait.

Too small.

I want it to dominate the screen.

Example scale:

today is about
the antler deck.

everything else
can wait.

Use 42–52px sizing.

Maximum 3–4 lines.

Large vertical spacing.

The thesis should immediately communicate:

Donna understands what matters.

The thesis should occupy roughly 25–35% of the first viewport.

---

## EMOTIONAL DESIGN SYSTEM

Every block must carry emotional intent.

Available tones:

* witness
* celebration
* confrontation
* reflection
* invitation
* reminder
* permission

Do NOT show tone labels.

Express tone through:

* spacing
* typography
* warmth
* border treatment
* motion

Example:

Confrontation:
slightly stronger contrast
slightly tighter composition

Reflection:
more breathing room
softer typography

Celebration:
warmer accent
more openness

Permission:
lighter visual weight

No emoji.

No badges.

No loud indicators.

---

## CREATE A SIGNATURE VISUAL IDENTITY

The product currently lacks a unique visual idea.

Create a persistent visual system called:

Memory Threads

Memory Threads represent relationships Donna has learned.

Examples:

pitch nerves

sleep

yc

priya

focus

These should appear subtly throughout the app.

Not as a graph widget.

As a living visual language.

Thin organic lines.

Soft connections.

Slow movement.

Very subtle animation.

The user should feel:

"My life is connected."

Not:

"This is a graph."

Memory Threads should appear:

* on Plan
* in Memory
* occasionally in Chat
* during screen transitions

This becomes Donna's signature.

---

## MAKE MEMORY THE MOST BEAUTIFUL SCREEN

Memory should become the hero feature.

Current memory graph feels auto-generated.

Avoid network graph libraries.

Instead create a handcrafted visualization.

Think:

constellations

mind maps

relationship diagrams

floating memories

organic positioning

large whitespace

animated breathing nodes

The center should always be:

YOU

Around it:

Projects

People

Goals

Patterns

Observations

The screen should feel magical.

When users open Memory they should immediately understand:

Donna remembers.

Donna connects.

Donna understands.

---

## REDESIGN CHAT COMPLETELY

Current chat looks like ChatGPT.

This is unacceptable.

The chat experience must reinforce memory.

Introduce inline cognitive components.

Examples:

---

You mentioned this before

Three weeks ago before your last pitch
you were worried about the same slide.

---

Pattern noticed

Sleep drops by roughly one hour
before every major review.

---

Related memory

Priya has challenged pricing
three times in previous discussions.

---

These should feel native to the conversation.

Not separate widgets.

Chat should feel like a conversation with context.

Not a blank LLM interface.

The user should constantly feel:

Donna remembers.

---

## PLAN PAGE REDESIGN

Desired hierarchy:

1. Thesis
2. Today's Shape
3. Open Loops
4. One Nudge
5. Reflection

Remove visual clutter.

Reduce boxes.

Use more editorial composition.

Today's Shape should become a beautiful vertical rhythm.

Example:

11:00
1:1 with Priya

14:00
Deep Work

18:00
Review

Not a calendar.

A shape of the day.

A narrative.

---

## SIGNALS PAGE REDESIGN

Current implementation feels like health dashboard cards.

I want observations.

Not metrics.

Instead of:

Sleep
6.2h

Show:

Sleep has been slipping as review week approaches.

Then:

6.2h last night
7.3h baseline

Observation first.
Data second.

Human interpretation over numbers.

Always.

---

## PREMIUM MOTION

Current interface feels static.

Introduce:

* fade reveals
* staggered entrances
* memory thread movement
* ambient transitions
* subtle depth shifts

No spring animations.

No bouncing.

No flashy interactions.

Everything should feel calm and expensive.

Motion should resemble:

Apple Journal
Arc
Raycast

---

## TYPOGRAPHY

Typography should carry most of the hierarchy.

Use:

Instrument Serif
for emotional and editorial moments.

Inter
for interface content.

Large type.

Aggressive use of whitespace.

Comfortable reading rhythm.

Typography should feel like a beautifully designed magazine.

---

## COLOR SYSTEM

Current palette is too safe.

Create a richer, more premium palette.

Morning:

Background:
#F6F2EC

Text:
#191816

Secondary:
#8A7F76

Accent Rust:
#B45B38

Border:
#E8DED4

Night:

Background:
#0E0D0C

Card:
#171513

Text:
#EEE8E1

Secondary:
#A79D94

Accent Rust:
#D06A45

Border:
#292421

The rust accent should appear sparingly.

At most 5% of the screen.

When it appears, it should matter.

---

## FINAL GOAL

When a YC partner sees the product for 10 seconds:

They should NOT think:

"AI assistant."

They should think:

"This feels like a new category."

The application should feel like:

a memory-native operating system for your life.

Prioritize emotional resonance over feature visibility.

Prioritize understanding over organization.

Prioritize identity over convention.

Make Donna memorable.

#   the remainder still processes here. Lets you test locally without
#   touching the Meta dashboard each session.
RELAY_URL=
DEV_RELAY_URL=
DEV_PHONE_NUMBERS=

# Audio
# ElevenLabs (TTS — outbound voice notes). Flash v2.5 ≈ 200ms latency.
# Override ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID for a different persona.
# ELEVENLABS_MODEL_ID is the TTS model.
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=
ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID=WAhoMTNdLdMoq1j3wf3I
ELEVENLABS_MODEL_ID=eleven_flash_v2_5
# ELEVENLABS_VOICE_SPEED: 0.7 (slow) – 1.2 (fast). Default 1.2 = max snappiness.
ELEVENLABS_VOICE_SPEED=1.2
# Deepgram (STT — inbound voice notes). Nova-3 multilingual.
DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=
DEEPGRAM_MODEL=nova-3
# Voice feature flag. When false: the voice_response marker in send_burst is
# stripped (Donna falls back to text); inbound transcription still runs.
DONNA_VOICE_ENABLED=true
# Hard cap on character count synthesized per turn. Past this we fall back to
# text. WA voice notes feel wrong past ~600 chars (≈45s) anyway.
DONNA_VOICE_MAX_CHARS=600

# Image generation (fal). When unset, the image tool degrades to text.
FAL_KEY=
# FAL_IMAGE_MODEL=fal-ai/flux/schnell

# Web search (Exa) for web_search / agentic_web_search / research tools.
# When unset, those tools return "web search unavailable".
EXA_API_KEY=
